{
  "_comment": "Copy this file to whatsapp.json (same folder) and fill it with this project's real WhatsApp profiles — ONLY needed for multiple identities or a project-local message store; a single instance works from WAHA_BASE_URL + WAHA_WHATSAPP_API_KEY in env with no json. NON-SECRET WIRING ONLY. Each top-level object key (besides 'default'/'messages_dir') is a profile name. 'secret_env' names the env var holding that instance's X-Api-Key — set the value in the project's .env / .env.local (gitignored), NEVER here. Optional 'engine'/'tier' pin the expected WAHA mode that `whatsapp health` validates against (default engine GOWS; omit 'tier' to skip the tier check). Delete this _comment line in the real whatsapp.json.",
  "default": "<profile-name>",
  "messages_dir": "messages",
  "<profile-name>": {
    "base_url": "https://waha.example.com",
    "session": "default",
    "number": "15551234567",
    "mode": "read",
    "engine": "GOWS",
    "secret_env": "WAHA_WHATSAPP_API_KEY"
  }
}
